The Lagos State Ram Sellers Association has successfully elected new officials to run the affairs of the association for the next four years. Alhaji Ibrahim Mustapha Alkali, was elected chairman. He defeated his rival, Alhaji Lauga. The election was conducted by the electoral committee of the group and observed by the Nigeria Police Force, State Security Services (SSS), Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), representative of Arewa Community in Lagos, Alhaji Musa Saleh, the secretary general of the community and Northern Nigeria Youths Organisation, Alhaji Sani Sulisu Dantaqa. In his acceptance speech, the chairman of the Association, Alhaji Alkali who won the election, thanked every members of the group, promising not to let them down. He urged every members of the group to support him to deliver good leadership. “I want all ram sellers association of Lagos State chapter to come together for the progress of our group and I promise to give listening ear to everyone that comes with good advice. The election committee chairman, Alhaji Hassan Magorori, who said the process was transparent, urged the members to bury their differences and work as one. The secretary general of the Arewa community urged the new chairman- elect to carry every members of the group along for progress of the group and Lagos State. “Leadership is a big test given to you by your group. Don’t let them down, build good relationship with your members, and carry them along both those that are not here for progress of the group.